NEW DIGITAL PHONES

Three rival manufacturers are set to launch digital cellular phones.
Alcatel is offering two new GSM handportables, the HC600 and HC400,
while Oki will launch its first GSM product, the GT1.  In addition,
Ericsson will launch the DF363 and DH362, two handportables based on
the US digital Amps standard.





