KYUSHU SERVICE OPENS

The Tu-Ka Cellular/Digital Phone group's joint venture digital cellular
network in Kyushu, Japan, has started commercial services four months
ahead of schedule.  Digital Tu-Ka Kyushu will initially cover the
capital city, major highways and railway lines, reaching 80 per cent of
the region's 14 million population.  The network will be expanded to 90-
per-cent coverage next year.





