     McDonnell Douglas (MD) will launch additional 15 satellites

     McDonnell Douglas (MD) will launch additional 15 satellites
for use in Iridium's operations and maintenance phase.  Birds will
be boosted into low earth orbit on Delta 2/7420 rockets on 5
launches carrying 3 satellites each.  Flights from Vandenberg Air
Force Base, Cal., will begin in April 1998 and continue through
July 2000.  MD already is contracted to launch 40 Iridium
satellites that will mark start of constellation's deployment.



