COPYRIGHT 1995-6 M2 COMMUNICATIONS LTD
 
ERICSSON AB is confident that it holds key patents
for CDMA wireless technology which it may consider
licensing to competing companies.  Lars Ramqvist,
managing director of the company, believes that the
firm could make significant revenues from this
holding even though the company itself prefers TDMA
over CDMA as the integral basis for systems. Ramqvist
was keen to point out that Ericsson will permit fair,
equitable use of the patents and will not attempt to
block any licensed use.




