 NTT AND KDD SHOULD MERGE, SAYS MINISTER


Japan's International Trade and Industry Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto has proposed a merger between the country's largest
domestic and international telecoms firms, NTT and KDD, to
strengthen its position in the international market, reports
Reuters. He suggested that domestic telecom lines should open up
further, while NTT and KDD banded together to compete
internationally by linking domestic and overseas lines.
Hashimoto, also Liberal Democratic Party president, made the
suggestion during a television talk show.






