<A NAME = "29"></A>Copyright
TELECOM MARKETS via NewsNet
January 18, 1996

ROME DROPS TARIFF INCREASE

The Italian government has frozen controversial changes to telephone
charges in the face of unexpectedly heavy criticism.  The post and
telecommunications ministry said that it had not withdrawn the tariff
rebalancing decrees -- which would increase the cost of local calls --
but would be talking to unions before implementing the measures.





