HUNGARIAN SALE

The Hungarian government agreed to sell a further 37-per-cent stake in
telecommunications operator Matav to the MagyarCom consortium, which is
equally owned by Ameritech and Deutsche Telekom (Telecom Markets,
282/17).  MagyarCom will pay $852 million to the state privatisation
agency, giving it a 67-per-cent majority holding in Matav.





