<A HREF ="#HeadList">Back to Headline List</A><BR>
<HR>
<A NAME = "41"></A>Copyright
TELECOM MARKETS via NewsNet
January 18, 1996

AT&T CUTS

AT&T has announced plans to cut 40,000 jobs over the next three years,
including 30,000 involuntary redundancies, as it reorganises its
business into three core units (Telecom Markets, 277/6).  The services
unit will lose 17,000 jobs (to reduce its total workforce to 110,000)
and the manufacturing unit will lose 23,000.  The demerger will cost $6
billion (#3.8 billion) before tax and AT&T will take a charge of $4
billion net against earnings in the fourth quarter of 1995 to cover the
restructuring.





